# Design System Rule — Ant Design (Test Environment)

For testing and rapid UI prototyping, the project uses **Ant Design (antd)** as the default design system.

AI must prefer **Ant Design components** when generating UI code.

---

# Library

UI components should be imported from:

antd

Example

import { Button, Input, Form, Card } from "antd"

---

# Usage Guidelines

When generating UI components:

- Prefer Ant Design components over custom UI
- Avoid implementing custom components that already exist in Ant Design
- Use Ant Design layout components when possible

Examples

Layout  
Form  
Table  
Card  
Modal  
Tabs  
Dropdown

---

# Styling Rules

Avoid custom CSS when Ant Design props can achieve the same result.

Preferred approach

Ant Design props  
↓  
Ant Design layout components  
↓  
Minimal custom styling

---

# Component Examples

Preferred usage

<Button type="primary">Submit</Button>

<Input placeholder="Enter email" />

<Form>
  <Form.Item label="Email">
    <Input />
  </Form.Item>
</Form>

---

# Prototyping Rule

During early development or testing:

- Use Ant Design components directly
- Do not prematurely create custom UI components

Custom UI components should only be created when:

- design system is finalized
- reusable component abstraction is required

---

# Integration With Project Architecture

Ant Design components should be used inside:

widgets  
features  
pages

Atomic UI components in:

shared/ui

may wrap Ant Design components when needed.

Example

shared/ui/button/Button.tsx

which internally uses

antd Button

When possible, prefer Ant Design components instead of creating new UI components.
